    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Senators Regret Remarks on Troops'' (news article, March 2):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Senators Regret Remarks on Troops'' (news article, March 2):</p>
        <p>So Senator John McCain and Senator Barack Obama have both apologized for saying that American lives have been ''wasted'' in battle.</p>
        <p>But while no one is questioning the noble efforts made by our troops and the sacrifices so many of them have made, the war in Iraq is still a mistake. And more lives sacrificed will almost certainly not improve the result.</p>
        <p>If anyone should apologize, it should be President Bush for sending Americans over there in the first place.</p>
        <p>Janice Hough  Palo Alto, Calif., March 3, 2007</p>
      </block>
